{"lemma":"رِباطِ","slug":"رِباطِ","root":"ر.ب.ط","root_slug":"ر-ب-ط","root_link":"/words/roots/ر-ب-ط","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun_prop","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"رِباط","root":"ربط","pos":"N","occurrence_count":1},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":4},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n14509","n14511"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B1%D9%90%D8%A8%D8%A7%D8%B7%D9%90"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of رَابَطَ (rābaṭa) (form III)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"A thing with which one ties, binds or makes fast: tie, band, ribbon, ligature, bondage, bond, fetter"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"ribat (a frontier post where travellers (particularly soldiers) could stay)"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"viburnum"}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/ri.baːtˤ/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n14509","headword_ar":"رِبَاطٌ","root":"rbT","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A thing with which one ties, binds,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"makes fast,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a skin,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and a beast,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"&c.;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a rope with which a beast is tied:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rubuTN","text_ar":"رُبُطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ruboTN","text_ar":"رُبْطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, TA;) the latter a contraction of the former: (TA:) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mirobaTN","text_ar":"مِرْبَطٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mirobaTapN","text_ar":"مِرْبَطَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"also signify"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a thing with which a beast is tied."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) It is said in a prov.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ino *ahaba EayorN faEayorN fiY Alr~ibaATi","text_ar":"اـِنْ ذَهَبَ عَيْرٌ فَعَيْرٌ فِى الرِّبَاطِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"If an ass is gone away, an ass is tied to the cord"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: relating to contentment with what is present and relinquishment of what is absent. (Mgh.) [See also 3.] ―         -b2-  [Hence,] used by the vulgar in the sense of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^uxo*apN","text_ar":"اُخْذَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A kind of fascination by which enchantresses withhold their husbands from other women."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ax*","text_ar":"اخذ"},{"kind":"text","text":".) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A snare for catching game."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Mgh.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaTaEa AlZ~aboYu ribaATahu","text_ar":"قَطَعَ الظَّبْىُ رِبَاطَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The gazelle rent his snare"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S.) ―         -b4-  (assumed tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"heart:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) as though the body were tied thereby. (TA.) Hence, (TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qrD","text_ar":"قرض"},{"kind":"text","text":",)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaraDa rbaATahu","text_ar":"قَرَضَ ربَاطَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He died:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M and K in that art.:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he was at the point of death."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K in that art.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaA='a fulaAnN waqado qaraDa ribaATahu","text_ar":"جَا=ءَ فُلَانٌ وَقَدْ قَرَضَ رِبَاطَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one came having turned away,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"back, harassed, distressed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fatigued,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA, and AZ and Az in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qrD","text_ar":"قرض"},{"kind":"text","text":",)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and at the point of death:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AZ, Az:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"harassed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"distressed, by thirst,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by fatigue:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qrD","text_ar":"قرض"},{"kind":"text","text":":) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in a state of intense thirst and hunger."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M in that art.) ―         -b5-  (assumed tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"spirit:"},{"kind":"text","text":"as in the saying of El-'Ajjáj, describing a wild bull,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"fabaAta wahowa vaAbitu Alr~ibaATi"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And he passed the night firm in spirit"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.)       -A2-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rabiyTN","text_ar":"رَبِيطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (of which it is a pl., or pl. pl.,) in three places.       -A3-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A single building of those which are called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ribaATaAtN","text_ar":"رِبَاطَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, K:) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a public building for the accommodation of travellers and their beasts;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bariydN","text_ar":"بَرِيدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":";) an application well known, and mentioned in the TK:]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a religious house,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"house inhabited by devotees; a dwelling for Soofees;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(El-Makreezee's “ Khitat ” ii. 427;) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a hospice,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an asylum for poor Muslim students and others,"},{"kind":"text","text":"like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zaAwiyapN","text_ar":"زَاوِيَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":";]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a building for the poor:"},{"kind":"text","text":"in this sense post-classical: pl., accord. to analogy,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rubuTN","text_ar":"رُبُطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ribaATaAtN","text_ar":"رِبَاطَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Msb.)"}],"source_refs":["S","Msb","K","Mgh","TA","AZ","Az"]},{"entry_id":"n14511","headword_ar":"رَبَّاطٌ","root":"rbT","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"One who ties bow-strings."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"}],"source_refs":[]}]},"classical_definitions":null}